docs.text: eddie murphy has a lot riding on harlem nights .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: as the movie's writer , director , executive producer , and star , murphy will shoulder all of the blame if harlem nights fails .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: but at the same time , he'll receive all of the credit if it succeeds .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: should you sacrifice your hard-earned cash to support murphy's risky gamble ?
docs.label: negative

docs.text: well , that depends on whom you trust more : me or eddie murphy .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: here's what murphy thinks : " i think the audience is expecting a good time .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: they gonna get sexy .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: they gonna get funny .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: they gonna get drama .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: they gonna get all of that .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: i think it's the best movie i've done " ( paramount radio network ) .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: here's what i think : harlem nights is charmless , unoriginal , disappointing , and almost without question , the worst film of the actor's career ( i haven't seen best defense ) .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: and guess who's to blame ? !
docs.label: negative

docs.text: the movie's problem is not murphy's direction : harlem nights is a fairly good looking film .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: no , the project was probably doomed even before the cameras rolled .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: murphy's awful script is the culprit .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: let's count the mistakes he makes in his first attempt at screenwriting :
docs.label: negative

docs.text: ( 1 ) murphy shatters the record for the most profanity in a motion picture .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: yes , he even outdoes his own work in raw .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: practically every line of dialogue in harlem nights contains at least one four letter word .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: and after 15 minutes , it gets irritating .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: ( 2 ) murphy wastes the talents of his fine cast .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: richard pryor , redd foxx , michael lerner , and della reese face the impossible task of carving out credible characters from a script riddled with stereotypes .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: each of them shines occasionally , but basically what we have are good performers stuck in a bad vehicle .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: ( 3 ) the movie demeans women by depicting them solely as sexual objects and as pawns in power struggles between men .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: murphy has admitted in interviews that he is weary of women in his private life , which is really neither here nor there .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: but when murphy puts his bitter feelings on 3 , 000 movie screens across the country , it's another matter altogether .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: you're forced to swallow some pretty gruesome stuff .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: for instance , murphy punches della reese in the stomach .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: and he shoots jasmine guy in the head .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: this is a mean-spirited movie , folks !
docs.label: negative

docs.text: lovely newcomer lela rochon gets off easy in her role as a common whore , but only because she doesn't have any scenes with murphy .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: thank god : he might have run her over with a bulldozer .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: ( 4 ) murphy has written for himself perhaps his blandest role to date .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: the loveable eddie murphy charisma emerges only once or twice during the film .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: murphy would rather give his character a spiffy wardrobe than a spiffy personality .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: sometimes it seems as if murphy made harlem nights just so he could wear fancy suits and look debonair .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: ( 5 ) the plot is a shameless rip-off of the sting .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: if you're going to make another sting movie , you've got to do something original .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: murphy's tale of warring nightclub owners in harlem ( circa 1938 ) fails to add anything new to the formula .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: ( 6 ) to get laughs , murphy makes fun of stuttering .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: you know a comedy is digging deep when it resorts to ridiculing the handicapped .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: ( 7 ) murphy's idea of drama is a scene in which his character apologizes for the first time in his life .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: for what ?
docs.label: negative

docs.text: for shooting reese's little toe off !
docs.label: negative

docs.text: needless to say , murphy shows little , if any , promise or imagination as a screenwriter .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: in all fairness , however , a few rays of sunshine do manage to break through the gloomy cloud surrounding the movie .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: danny aiello is fun to watch as a dirty cop on the take .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: aiello stands out in the large , ensemble cast : he obviously relishes the opportunity to play such a nasty character ( a racist detective with mob ties ) .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: aiello's zesty performance gives harlem nights some much needed spice .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: another bright spot is arsenio hall , who has a hilarious , show-stopping cameo as a cry-baby gangster ; hall virtually steals the spotlight from murphy .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: in fact , hall's ten minutes on screen are the funniest ten minutes in the movie .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: unfortunately , his character is completely irrelevant to the plot ; murphy should have given hall a much bigger role .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: of course , i've already mentioned that i didn't care for murphy's character , but i have to admit that i did love his neckties .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: they are simply spectacular--almost worth the price of admission .
